article.headline: Butler 65, Evansville 64
article.story: INDIANAPOLIS (AP) -- Mike Monserez hit two free throws with five seconds left to lift Butler to a 65-64 over Evansville on Saturday. Monserez finished with 17 points for Butler (3-2), which snapped a two-game losing streak and had its third-straight game decided at the free throw line. Monserez, who has struggled with his shot of late, scored seven in the final four minutes, and went 5-for-14 from the field and 5-of-6 from the free-throw line. Avery Sheets had 14 points on 6-of-9 shooting, while Duane Lightfoot added 13 despite a sprained ankle that had threatened to keep him out of the lineup. Andre Burton scored 16 points for the Purple Aces, who fell to 0-4, and was among four players in double figures. Clint Cuffle had 13 points and nine rebounds, and Kyle Anslinger added 11 off the bench. Evansville led 32-25 at halftime and by as many as 10 points in the second half, but Bruce Horan's 3-pointer with less than two minutes in ignited a 14-4 Butler run spanning more than three minutes. The Bulldogs went to the foul line 10 times during the run, converting on six attempts. The Purple Aces, led by Matt Webster's 3-for-3, managed only 10 foul shots for the game. The game was Butler's third in a week decided by two points or less. Butler lost to Ball State on Wednesday as the Cardinals hit two free throws with four seconds left for a 63-61 victory and again on Nov. 30th to Michigan, 61-60 in overtime, on a pair of free throws with 6.9 second left.
